<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="338" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d338">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-10-23"><hi rend="italic">October 23,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch, No. 393, of the 8th ultimo, transmitting a report, prepared by
                            Mr. Williams, Chinese secretary of the legation, on the production and
                            taxation of opium in China.</p>
                        <p>You will say to Mr. Williams that the department appreciates his
                            excellent report, and that it has been read with interest.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">E. Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>